nt nuclear weapons will be signed Sunday. However, Iran's Foreign Ministry spokesperson stated an agreement is unlikely to be signed immediately, suggesting further negotiations are needed.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/youre-getting-discombobulated-commander-in-chief-trump-shares-ai-image-of-us-troops-advancing/articleshow/131714688.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/youre-getting-discombobulated-commander-in-chief-trump-shares-ai-image-of-us-troops-advancing/articleshow/131714688.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-14T07:50:09+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131715094,imgsize-1546928.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Fans thought Gensyxa destroyed her new streaming setup until they noticed one detail]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131712294.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Russian streamer Gensyxa's video of her streaming room flooding went viral, captivating millions who believed it was a genuine accident. The footage showed a rapid deluge, damaging expensive equipment and furniture, creating a sensation online. However, it later emerged the flooded room might have been a staged set for the video, sparking further discussion about its authenticity and safety.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/fans-thought-gensyxa-destroyed-her-new-streaming-setup-until-they-noticed-one-detail/articleshow/131712294.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/fans-thought-gensyxa-destroyed-her-new-streaming-setup-until-they-noticed-one-detail/articleshow/131712294.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-14T02:03:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1